<SLUG> BC-Sports-Basebal-US Roundup, 2nd Add,0218 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNDATED: seven hits. Rangers 8, Padres 7 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   In Arlington, Texas, Juan Gonzalez hit his 19th homer and had
three RBIs to boost his major league-leading total to 76 as Texas
beat San Diego.
	   Gonzalez homered off former Rangers pitcher Kevin Brown in the
sixth inning and also had an RBI double in the second and a
sacrifice fly in the fourth.
	   Tim Crabtree (3-0) retired the final batter in the seventh to
pick up the victory, and John Wetteland pitched the ninth for his
15th save.
 &UR; Giants 3, Cardinals 2 &QC; 
	   In St. Louis, after missing three games with back spasms, Mark
McGwire didn't waste any time resuming his chase of Roger Maris'
home run record.
	   However, his major league-leading 28th homer wasn't enough to
prevent another loss for the St. Louis Cardinals.
	   McGwire hit a two-run homer off Orel Hershiser in his first
at-bat Friday night, but Hershiser (6-3) recovered to win his sixth
straight decision in San Francisco's 3-2 victory in the opener of
the only non-interleague series of the weekend.
	   Jeff Kent had a two-run double in the third for the Giants, who
won their season-high seventh straight and sent the Cardinals to
their sixth loss in seven games. Kent Bottenfield (1-3) took the
loss.
</TEXT>
