<SLUG> BC-Sports-Auto Racing-Le Mans 24 Hours,0200 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Schneider leads qualifying for Le Mans 24 Hours 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: RECAPS to CORRECT that Webber is Australian sted Austrian.
<TEXT>
	   LE MANS (AP) _ A Mercedes CLK-LM will be in the lead Saturday
for the Le Mans 24 Hours endurance race after posting the fastest
times in the practice sessions.
	   Germany's Bernd Schneider, who is driving with another German,
Kieurs Ludwig. and Australian Mark Webber, recorded the fastest
time of 3 minutes, 35.544 seconds in the trials, an average speed
of 227 kph (141.14 mph).
	   One of last year's winners, Italy's Michele Alboreto, posted a
time of 3:40.503 in a Porsche LMP leaving him in ninth place after
the final practice sessions, which finished at midnight Thursday.
	   Alboreto's partners this year are Stephan Johannson of Sweden,
part of last year's successful team, and France's Yannick Dalmas.
	   The highly-rated team of Martin Brundle, Emmanuel Collard and
Eric Helary came second in practice with a time of 3:36.552 in a
Toyota GT1.
	   GT1 cars filled the top five places.
	   The highest place prototype car was the BMW V12 LM driven by
Pierluigi Martini in sixth.
</TEXT>
