<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-No Foreign Experts </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Don't depend on foreign experts to sort out Malaysia's economic problems: Mahathir 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad on
Saturday once again exhorted Malaysians not to rely on foreign
experts to solve their country's economic ills.
	   Countries that have turned to outside advice have all
experienced economic turmoil, the outspoken leader said in a speech
at the National Palace to celebrate the birthday of Malaysia's
king.
	   Their reliance on foreign expertise only brought these countries
political instability, massive unemployment, surging bankruptcies
and escalating inflation, he warned.
	   Mahathir said all this could happen in Malaysia if more pressure
was imposed on the ringgit and the local stock exchange. But he
said the government had taken several measures to revive the
nation's economy.
	   He said the people's faith and confidence in the government were
vital because not all the government's measures could be publicly
announced.
	   Steps to support the ringgit include reducing imports and
encouraging prudent spending, he said.
	   Touching on recovery, he said it would not come easy, but he was
confident that reducing the country's dependence on foreign
exchange ``we will somewhat escape the threats of attacks on our
currency and the nation's economy'' he said.
	   He said the Malaysia would use the ringgit and other local
currencies in its trade with other countries.
</TEXT>
