<SLUG> BC-AP News Digest,1160 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0600 GMT:
	   NEW:
	   _BRITAIN-DIANA-AL FAYED. British newspapers criticize Al Fayed's
remarks about Diana's mother.
	   _GERMANY-ERITREAN EVACUATION. Foreigners evacuated from Eritrea
tell of rising tension.
	   _ITALY-PLUNDERED ART. Seventeen plundered Italian art works
identified in Germany.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   UNITED NATIONS _ Hoping to curb the arms race in South Asia, the
Security Council reaches tentative agreement on a Japanese
resolution urging India and Pakistan to halt nuclear weapons
programs and denying them status as nuclear states.
UN-INDIA-PAKISTAN. Has moved; council vote set for Saturday after
1430 GMT. By Robert H. Reid.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _INDIA-NUCLEAR. Indian official says sanctions will not slow
economic reforms.
	   ASMARA, Eritrea _ Ethiopian warplanes bomb an air force base
outside Asmara, then are shot down by anti-aircraft guns, bringing
the border dispute between the two East African nations right to
Eritrea's capital. ERITREA-ETHIOPIA. Has moved; developments will
be expedited. By Julia Stewart. AP Photos AMS101-108.
