<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Singapore-Digital TV </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Singapore to test U.S., Japanese, European digital TV 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   SINGAPORE (AP) _ The competing digital television systems of
Japan, the United States and Europe will be tested in Singapore
this year, and officials will decide which to adopt within a year ,
officials were quoted Saturday as saying.
	   The three standards for the new high-definition television were
demonstrated for the first time together at the BroadcastAsia '98
trade show in Singapore during the past week.
	   ``None of the three standards has been perfected. Each has its
own shortcomings and price tag,'' Yatiman Yusof, a member of
parliament who oversees information and the arts, told The Straits
Times after watching a demonstration of the three systems.
	   The paper quoted Lim Hock Chuan, chief executive officer of the
Singapore Broadcasting Authority, as saying the government expects
to pick one of the systems within a year.
	   No Southeast Asian nation has decided on a digital system.
</TEXT>
