<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Monk Russian Roulette </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Buddhist monk charged with murder in Russian roulette killing 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ A Buddhist monk has been charged with
murder and two others were defrocked after a man died while they
were playing Russian roulette with a pistol.
	   The death is the latest in a series of scandals ranging from
corruption to rape and murder involving the normally revered clergy
in this overwhelmingly Buddhist country.
	   The monks and a layman were playing the game Thursday, in which
they took turns pointing a revolver loaded with a single bullet at
each other's heads and pulled the trigger, newspapers reported
Saturday.
	   The gun finally went off and killed the layman, Ritthirong
Khachawitee, who had apparently had brought the gun to the Wat Wang
Sala temple in the eastern town of Kanchanaburi and invited the
monks, whom he knew, to play with it.
	   Police charged Samart Phakphum, the temple's vice abbot, with
murder Friday. He was defrocked, as were the two others.
	   Police were quoted by The Nation newspaper as saying there had
been no previous reports about the monks misbehaving and they had
not been drinking when they started the game.
	   In traditional Russian roulette, a player points a partially
loaded gun at his own head and pulls the trigger.
</TEXT>
