<HEADLINE>
Chinese authorities execute man for armed robbery 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ Authorities in the southern province of Guangdong
have executed a man convicted of stealing 300,000 yuan from a taxi
passenger and severely injuring a soldier while trying to escape,
the state-run Liberation Army Daily reported Saturday.
	   The Shaoguan Intermediate People's Court sentenced Zhong
Wangxing to death at a public rally on Friday and fined him 20,000
yuan (dlrs 2,421) for the Dec. 13 robbery, the report said.
	   It said the execution was conducted shortly after sentencing.
	   According to the report, Zhong used a cleaver to force his way
into a taxi and to seize the money. A female soldier who attempted
to capture him suffered serious injuries and hearing loss after
Zhong slashed her with the knife.
	   Six other people from Zhong's village who attempted to help him
escape were being tried separately, the report added.
</TEXT>
