<HEADLINE>
Two Thai undercover officers released by drug dealers 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MAE SOT, Thailand (AP) _ A gang of drug traffickers who took two
undercover narcotics officers hostage released their captives and
fled Saturday as more than 100 police were closing in on them.
	   A police spokesman, speaking on condition of anonymity, said
that the five hostage-takers and three other gang members tried to
flee the hilly area and that two had been arrested.
	   The rest were on the run in the rugged terrain around Mae Sot,
370 kilometers (230 miles) northwest of Bangkok. The freed officers
were flown to the capital for debriefing.
	   The officers were unmasked as undercover men Thursday while
posing as buyers in an amphetamine deal. They were beaten by their
captors, who demanded 3 million baht (dlrs 75,000) for their
release.
</TEXT>
