<HEADLINE>
Sri Lanka's Jayawardena hits maiden century 
</HEADLINE>
AP Photo Planned
<TEXT>
	   GALLE, Sri Lanka (AP) _ Sri Lanka's rising star Mahela
Jayawardena hammered his maiden century Saturday as his team went
in for lunch at 275 for 6 in reply to New Zealand's 193 on the
fourth day of the second Test in this southern city.
	   The 21-year old Jayawardena, playing only his fourth Test,
stroked 17 fours off 240 balls in a stay at the crease lasting 296
minutes, after resuming from an overnight 88.
	   Sri Lanka however lost Arjuna Ranatunga for 36 early in the day
when he played a ball from off spinner Paul Wiseman to Shayne
O'Connor at mid-off.
	   Wiseman also picked up the wicket of Hashan Tillekaratne who was
bowled round his legs for 10, scored off 37 deliveries.
	   Sri Lanka's first innings lead over the tourists stood at 82 at
the interval. The match is being played in the stadium at Galle,
110 kilometers (70 miles) from the capital, Colombo.
</TEXT>
