<SLUG> BC-Sports-Bangladesh-World Cup-1st Ld Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDS : Minor changes in lead. Adds ``World Cup'' in slug. No pickup. Paramilitary to guard Bangladesh power stations during World Cup 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   DHAKA , Bangladesh (AP) _ Paramilitary forces will guard
Bangladeshi power stations during the World Cup to guard them from
possible attacks by soccer-crazy television viewers in case of
power outages, a senior official said Saturday.
	   Soldiers and police will take positions around all major power
stations 12 hours before the inauguration of the World Cup in
France on June 10, Nuruddin Mohammad Kamal, chairman of the
state-owned Power Development Board told reporters.
	   Soccer is the national game of Bangladesh, though its team did
not find place among the qualifiers for the World Cup.
	   Bangladesh, which needs over 2100 Megawatts of electricity each
year, generates only 1,700 Megawatts.
	   Major cities like Dhaka, Chittagong, Khulna and Rajshahi face
regular power outage and citizens have often taken to the streets
in violent demonstrations at power stations.
	    &UR; (hs, nnm)
</TEXT>
