<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Emergency Landing,0274 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
French plane forced to circle for hours before emergency landing 
</HEADLINE>
AP Photos ANK101-102
<TEXT>
	   ANTALYA, Turkey (AP) _ A French plane carrying passengers from a
Mediterranean holiday made an emergency landing Saturday in
Turkey's Antalya airport, after circling for hours.
	   AOM airline flight MD83 touched down at 1:40 a.m. (2240 GMT) on
its belly on the foam- covered runway of the Ataturk airport of
Antalya, television reports said.
	   None of the 157 passengers and six crew members were injured,
AOM airline said in a statement.
	   During the take off at 10:30 p.m. (1930 GMT) one of the plane's
tires was punctured, forcing the pilot to ask airport authorities
to prepare for an emergency landing.
	   ``We heard a big explosion following the takeoff,'' a French
passenger, only identified by his first name Nicolas, told private
ATV television as he left the plane.
	   Airport authorities asked the pilot to discharge some fuel in
the sea to lighten the plane. The pilot was unable to do so and
instead circled over the airport to reduce the aircraft's fuel
charge, authorities said.
	   The Anatolia news agency reported that the pilots sang to the
passengers to ease tension during this time.
	   The wheels of the plane collapsed during the landing, causing it
to skid across the runway on its belly.
	   All the passengers, on their way back to Paris after a holiday
in the popular resort city on Turkey's Mediterranean coast,
returned to the Club Mediterranee holiday resort for the night.
	   AOM said they would be flown back to Paris on Saturday
afternoon.
</TEXT>
