<SLUG> BC-Greece-Fake Money </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police arrest men with dlrs 160,000 in counterfeit money 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Police arrested three men believed linked
to an international counterfeiting ring early Saturday,
confiscating dlrs 160,000 worth of forged bills.
	   The three Greek nationals will be charged with possession of
counterfeit money with intent to sell, financial crimes squad
officials said.
	   The men were arrested in an open-air parking lot in the central
Greek city of Lamia while trying to negotiate a sale with an
unknown party. Police found 50,000 forged bills in 10,000-drachma
(dlrs 30) denominations, along with two forged Russian passports.
	   In March, police arrested a man in Athens with dlrs 562,000
worth of U.S. and Greek counterfeit currency and computer equipment
used to produce the fake bills.
