<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-India-Religious Riots,0251 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fresh Hindu-Muslim rioting kills three in southern India 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   HYDERABAD, India (AP) _ Fanatic Hindus and Muslims clashed in at
least half a dozen places in the southern Indian city of Hyderabad
for the second straight day Saturday, killing at least three people
and injuring 40 more, police said.
	   Police fired gunshots to disperse the rioters who attacked each
other with swords, knives and stones in the capital of Andhra
Pradesh state, said Ram Pratap Singh, the city police chief.
	   Those killed included a police officer whose home was attacked,
Singh said. Police imposed curfew as nearly 1,500 Hindus and
Muslims, split into at least six groups, rampaged through the
southern parts of the city, 1,300 kilometers (about 800 miles)
south of New Delhi.
	   Nearly 5,000 policemen fanned out and controlled the rioting
after nearly four hours. ``The situation is quite tense in the
city,'' Singh said.
	   Hyderabad's 5 million population is equally divided between
Hindus and Muslims.
	   Trouble erupted on Friday when Muslims, angered by pamphlets
denigrating their religion, attacked the Hindus after noon prayers.
At least 25 people were injured. They targeted homes, buses and
cars.
	   No one claimed responsibility for distributing the offensive
pamphlets.
	   Fresh rioting started Saturday after rumors spread that Hindus
had burned down a city mosque, Singh said. Six of the 40 injured
were hospitalized in serious condition.
</TEXT>
