<HEADLINE>
South Korea to close six diplomatic missions 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) _ South Korea will close its embassies
in Belgium, Uruguay, Cameroon, Zambia and Yugoslavia by August as
the government tightens its budget, Foreign Ministry officials said
Saturday.
	   The belt-tightening also forced South Korea to close its
consulate-general in Jidda of Saudi Arabia, the officials said.
	   Diplomatic operations in those missions will be taken over by
South Korean embassies in neighboring countries, they said.
	   South Korea called in the International Monetary Fund in
December to bail out its battered economy. Earlier this year, the
government said it planned to close 20 diplomatic missions overseas
to cut costs.
</TEXT>
