More shelling, more dead in Kosovo 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to RESTORE dropped word `is,' SUBS 4th graf to
DELETE garble, PICKUP 5th graf pvs.
By ISMET HAJDARI
Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Dozens of houses were aflame and
Serb gunners kept shelling villages in Kosovo, where another four
people were killed in fighting, ethnic Albanian and Serb sources
said Saturday.
	   The Kosovo Information Center, which is close to the ethnic
Albanian leadership in the Serb province, said fighting continued
Saturday in the Decani area, about 70 kilometers (45 miles) west of
provincial capital Pristina. The villages of Shaptej, Gramocel and
Babaloc were targeted by the Serbs' heavy artillery.
	    &UR; A 3-year-old child, identified as Leutrim Aga, was killed as he
slept in his bed in Gramocel and three other ethnic Albanians were
wounded in that village. Another ethnic Albanian was found dead in
nearby Babaloc.
	   Dozens of houses in the region were burning, the Kosovo
Information Center said. It also claimed that Serbian forces were
shelling along a border strip west of Djakovica, 75 kilometers (47
miles) southwest of Pristina, and that police reinforcements were
sent in.
