<HEADLINE>
Violent storm sweeps northern France, one person killed 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ A violent hail storm swept across northern France
on Saturday, killing one man who perished house when his house was
set on fire by lightning.
	   Several supermarkets were destroyed in the Pas-de-Calais region
near the English Channel. The hail ruined crops and turned roads
into rivers in a matter of minutes Saturday morning.
	   Houses were flooded, trees were downed and public parks filled
with debris near Bethune, a town 200 kilometers (123 miles)
northwest of Paris.
	   Weather officials predicted further storms in the area.
