<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Chess-World Chess Council,0179 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Shirov wins WCC tournament and faces Kasparov to fight for title 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   CAZORLA, Spain (AP) _ Spain's Alexei Shirov will face Gary
Kasparov in a World Chess Council championship match next fall
after defeating Vladimir Kramnik of Russia on Saturday in the WCC
challenger's competition in Spain.
	   Shirov, 25, who was born in Riga, Latvia, and is now a Spanish
citizen, beat Kramnik, 22, on the 48th move in the ninth game of
the match. His score went up to 5.5 after the win, with Kramnik
trailing him with 3.5.
	   Kramnik, who is seen by many as a future world champion and
ranked third after Russian Anatoly Karpov and Indian Viswanathan
Anand, lost concentration in his games and lost all chances of
taking the match when he was defeated by Shirov in the fourth game.
	   On Oct. 15 Spain's representative will try to claim the World
Chess Council championship in an 18-game match against title-holder
Kasparov that will be played in the southern city of Seville. The
second part of the match will be taken to Linares.
</TEXT>
