<HEADLINE>
May, Powell lead Hanshin in win against Yokohama 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Alonzo Powell drove in three runs and Darrel May
went the distance in a four-hit shutout, leading the Hanshin Tigers
to a 5-0 win over the Yokohama Baystars.
	   Powell, formerly of the Seattle Mariners, drove in one run with
a first-inning double before smashing a two-run homer in the fifth.
It was his sixth homerun of the year.
	   May, a left-hander formerly with the Anaheim Angels, struck out
10 and went the distance for his first win in Japan.
	   Yokohama starting pitcher Hiroki Nomura dropped to 4-4 after
giving up four runs on seven hits over five innings.
	   At the Nagoya Dome, the Yomiuri Giants Korean pitching star Cho
Sung-min earned his second complete-game shutout of the season as
Yomiuri trounced the Chunichi Dragons 10-0. It was Cho's sixth win
of the season against 2 losses.
	   Giants catcher Shinici Murata went 4-for-4 and drove in three
runs including his first homer of the season.
	   In Iwate, northern Japan, Mitsuru Manaka drove in three runs
with a bases-loaded triple in the eighth to push the Yakult
Swallows past the league-leading Hiroshima Carp 6-2.
	   Yakult hurler Kazuhisa Ishii struck out nine for the win,
improving to a record of 5-2.
	   In the Pacific League, Julio Franco, formerly of the Milwaukee
Brewers, hit a two-run homer and teammates Koichi Hori and Takashi
Tachikawa each followed with two-run homers of their own as the
Chiba Lotte Marines rolled over the the Nippon Ham Fighters 9-3.
	   Lotte starter Tomohiro Kuroki earned his fifth win after giving
up five hits over five innings.
	   At the Fukuoka Dome, Daiei's Koji Akiyama hit a three-run homer
and Chihiro Hamana drove in three runs to lift the Fukuoka Daiei
Hawks past the Kintetsu Buffaloes 10-4. With the victory, Daiei
moved into a tie for first place in the league with the Nippon Ham
Fighters.
	   Rain postponed a scheduled afternoon game between the Seibu
Lions and the Orix BlueWave.
