Flooding shuts airport in remote Russian region 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Floodwaters forced the closure of an airport
Saturday in the remote diamond-producing region of Yakutia, the
ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   Authorities said the flooding had destroyed portions of the
runway in the capital city of Yakutsk, about 4,800 kilometers
(3,000 miles) east of Moscow. The airport was closed until at least
Monday while the runway was repaired.
