<SLUG> BC-Germany-Missile Accident </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dutch pilot inadvertently drops missile on Bavarian field 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   GRAFENWOEHR, Germany (AP) _ A Dutch helicopter pilot fired wide
of the mark during missile practice on Saturday, hitting an open
field near a Bavarian town instead of a military training area.
	   The impact left a crater 50 centimeters (20 inches) deep and one
meter (yard) across about 500 meters (550 yards) from the intended
target area on U.S. military grounds, police said. No one was
injured.
	   The pilot was firing a J-model ``Hellfire'' missile as part of a
training exercise, the U.S. Seventh Army training command said in a
news release. The cause of the error was under investigation.
	   (cb-tsc)
</TEXT>
