<SLUG> BC-Sports-Auto Racing-Le Mans 24 Hours </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Toyota takes early lead in Le Mans 24 hour Race 
</HEADLINE>
EDS: After one hour, next update after 5 hours of race 1700GMT
<TEXT>
	   LE MANS, France (AP) - A Toyota GT One car driven by Martin
Brundle was ahead after the first hour of the Le Mans 24 Hour race
Saturday afternoon.
	   Brundle broke the course record on the third lap of the
endurance race, posting a time 3 minutes 42.817 seconds.
	   Brundle had completed 15 laps after the first hour of the race,
with an average speed of 214.019 kph.(133 mph)
	   Bernd Schneider's Mercedes CLK-LM, the fastest car in practice,
had also completed 15 laps.
	   Just behind was another Toyota GT One, driven by Belgium's
Thierry Boutsen, with an average speed of 212.854.
	   The car started in cloudy conditions, but after the first hour
the competitors were racing in fine mid-afternoon sunshine.
	   (ae-sz)	   
