Saturday.
	   ``It looks like it is the result of stormy winds in western
Georgia,'' said Gogi Makashvili, the deputy head of the Georgian
Energy Department. He said Georgian officials had sought help from
neighboring Azerbaijan, which was expected to supply emergency
electricity for Georgia's most vital needs.
