<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Austrian team arrives in Bordeaux 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   BORDEAUX, France (AP) _ Led by captain _ and pseudo-pilot _ Toni
Polster of FC Cologne, Austria's World Cup team arrived Saturday in
France.
	   Polster, always eager to provide a light moment, donned the
pilot's cap and posed for Austrian photographers in a quick visit
to the cockpit during the chartered two-hour flight to
Bordeaux-Merignac airport.
	   The Austrians will stay at the Relais de Margaux four-star
hotel, located some 20 kilometers (12.5 miles) north of this French
wine metropolis. Their first match is against Cameroon on Thursday.
	   At Arsac, not far from the hotel, the Austrian team planned a
light workout later in the day.
