<SLUG> BC-Britain-People-Billy Joel </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Billy Joel pulls out of British concerns - but Elton John goes ahead solo 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Suffering from a throat infection, American singer
Billy Joel pulled out of two more concerts with Sir Elton John on
Saturday and Sunday - but the shows will go on with the British
singer doing a solo act.
	   Joel also backed out of a joint concert Thursday in Manchester,
northern England because he was suffering from asthma and it was
canceled because promoters said Elton John would not appear alone.
	   But facing more disappointed fans in London, the British
singer-songwriter agreed to perform solo at Wembley Stadium.
	   During their joint concerts, the two stars face each other over
their pianos, swapping comments, and each makes an appearance in
the other's set.
	   At their opening concert in Glasgow, Scotland, on Tuesday, Joel,
49, suffered an acute asthma attack brought on by an upper
respiratory infection. Reviewers had noted bitter winds at the open
air concert.
	   Wembley Stadium has offered refunds to the 30,000 fans who have
booked tickets for each concert because Joel is not performing.
``But so far we have had only a handful of returns. People are
disappointed but happy to come and see Elton anyway,'' a
spokeswoman said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
	   The Wembley concerts would have been Joel's last in Britain. But
Joel and John still have 13 dates on their world tour, and it
wasn't clear whether the American singer would be able to perform.
	   Joel admitted on Friday he did not think he would be able to
``hack'' going on tour again.
	   ``In the old days I could scream and punch my way through it,
but now it wouldn't be fair to my fans,'' he said.
	   (eml)
</TEXT>
