<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian authorities seize plane; suspect radioactive cargo 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Ukrainian customs officials detained a
cargo plane Saturday after finding more than 40 tons of metal drums
emitting radioactivity, a news agency said.
	   It was not immediately clear whether the drums were filled with
a radioactive substance or if only the containers were
contaminated. There have been cases of contaminated containers
being illegally reused.
	   The plane, from Kazakstan, was seized when it made a refueling
stop in the western Ukrainian town of Rivne. It had been en route
to Russia from Germany.
