<SLUG> BC-India-Religious Riots, 1st Ld-Writethru,0308 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fresh Hindu-Muslim rioting kills four in southern India army asked to stand by, details. No pickup. ADDS byline. 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with four dead up from three, the
By OMER FAROOQ
Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
	   HYDERABAD, India (AP) _ Police fired gunshots to disperse Hindus
and Muslims who clashed in at least half a dozen places in the
southern Indian city of Hyderabad for a second day Saturday,
killing at least four people and injuring 40 others, police said.
	   Two people were killed by police fire and another two died of
stab wounds, said Ram Pratap Singh, the city police chief. The
rioters attacked each other with swords, knives and stones in the
capital of Andhra Pradesh state.
	   Those killed included a police officer whose home was attacked,
Singh said.
	   Police imposed a curfew as nearly 1,500 Hindus and Muslims,
split into at least six groups, rampaged through the southern parts
of the city, 1,300 kilometers (about 800 miles) south of New Delhi.
	   Nearly 5,000 policemen fanned out and controlled the rioting
after nearly four hours. ``The situation is quite tense in the
city,'' Singh said.
	   Singh said the military was asked to stand by in case rioting
broke out again.
	   Hyderabad's 5 million population is equally divided between
Hindus and Muslims.
	   Trouble erupted on Friday when Muslims, angered by pamphlets
denigrating their religion, attacked the Hindus after noon prayers.
At least 25 people were injured. They targeted homes, buses and
cars.
	   No one claimed responsibility for distributing the offensive
pamphlets.
	   Fresh rioting started Saturday after rumors spread that Hindus
had burned down a city mosque, Singh said. Six of the 40 injured
were hospitalized in serious condition.
</TEXT>
