<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Argentina,0223 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Passarella warns players to be careful with Japan 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   L'ETRAT, France (AP) _ Coach Daniel Passarella says Argentina
will take no chances when playing huge underdog Japan in their
World Cup opener June 14 in Toulouse.
	   ``Japan has a team that knows what it is doing, and works very
well in defense,'' Passarella said.
	   Passarella, who spoke to reporters late Friday, said he watched
Japan's 1-0 loss to Yugoslavia in a warmup match in Switzerland
last week and left the game with ``very much respect'' for the
Asians.
	   ``The Japanese in no way deserved that defeat,'' Passarella
said. ``They played to get more.''
	   Passarella noted that Japan has a strong defense which can
smoothly switch from man-to-man to zone marking. He has thus
ordered his defenders to simulate that change when marking Gabriel
Batistuta and Claudio Lopez, expected to be Argentina's starting
strikers.
	   There's little room to compare soccer history between two-time
world champion Argentina and Japan, which is making its World Cup
finals debut.
	   But, Argentines often remember what they felt was a humiliating
3-2 defeat to Japan in the 1964 Olympics in Tokyo.
	   Argentina and Japan will play in Group H, with Jamaica and
Croatia.
	   (eg/jw)
</TEXT>
