<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Golf-British Amateur, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spain's Sergio Garcia wins British Amateur Championship 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: ADDS quotes
<TEXT>
	   GULLANE, Scotland (AP) _ Sergio Garcia, expected to be Spain's
next great golfer, won the British Amateur Championship Saturday,
beating Craig Williams of Wales 7 and 6.
	   The 18-year-old Spaniard becomes the first player to hold both
the British Boys and British Amateur titles since countryman Jose
Maria Olazabal in 1984.
	   Garcia advanced to the final after winning a sudden-death
semifinal playoff Friday on the 23rd hole to beat Mark Hilton of
England.
	   He took a four-hole lead after the opening 18 Saturday and was
eight up after 26 holes on a day of on-and-off rain at Muirfield.
	   Garcia fell back to a six-hole advantage after losing the 27th
hole (No. 9), but won the 30th and halved the next two holes to
close out the Welshman.
	   Williams won his Friday semifinal 3 and 2 over Ben Mason of
England.
	   With the win, Garcia has qualified for July's British Open and
the U.S. Amateur in August. He's also qualified for next year's
Masters.
	   ``Now I've done it my next dream is to win the (British) Open,''
he said. ``This year? Well, I'll give it a try,''
	   (scw)	   
</TEXT>
