<BODY>
<SLUG> BC--Romania-Ship Seized </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Coast guard seizes Turkish ship poaching prized fish eggs 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   BUCHAREST, Romania (AP) _ After several warning shots, the coast
guard seized Saturday a Turkish ship after it crossed illegally
into Romanian waters to poach fish, an official said Saturday.
	   The fishermen aboard the Addoglu 2 had approached the Black Sea
port of Constanta to catch plaice, which lay their eggs near the
shore, said Coast Guard Commander Ion Dinea by telephone.
	   The poachers catch fish and then take out the roe which is
considered a delicacy.
	   Constanta is some 200 kilometers (125 miles) southeast of
Bucharest.
	   Dinea said the Turkish fishermen threw the plaice into the sea
in order to avoid being caught with the evidence. They surrendered
only after a second coast-guard ship joined in the pursuit and
fired warning shots.
	   Dinea said this was the 30th ship that crossed illegally into
Romanian waters this year.
	   Under Romanian law, the fishermen are liable to pay a fine of 10
million lei (almost dlrs 1,200). Their ship and fishing equipment
could be confiscated.
	   (ma/rp) 	   
</TEXT>
