for Del Piero's comeback. We must be careful with this kind of
injuries,'' doctor Andrea Ferretti said.
	   Del Piero, considered a key to Italy's success in the World Cup,
trained on his own Saturday as the other ``Azzurri'' kicked and
tackled in a brief game in Italy's first session on French soil at
the sports center of Senlis, north of Paris.
	   Baggio, who signed a two-year contract with Inter before flying
to France Friday, said he was looking forward to playing with
