<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Colombia,0241 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Cup: Colombia thinks only of Romania as World Cup approaches 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LA TUR DU PIN, France (AP) - For Colombia, the whole World Cup
experience comes down to one game _ its inaugural match against
Romania.
	   A victory over Romania not only would put Colombia en route to
the second round in a group that includes England and Tunisia, but
would also avenge its defeat in the inaugural game of USA '94
against the Romanians.
	   ``We have to win or win,'' Colombian coach Hernan Dario Gomez
said. ``We dream with avenging our failure of 1994, and to achieve
that, we have to beat Romania.''
	   ``It will be tough, but not impossible,'' said captain Carlos
Valderrama. ``We are anxious to bury the ghost'' of the last World
Cup.
	   England is a strong favorite to take the first place in the
group, and Colombia hopes a win over Romania would lift it to
second and allow it to advance the next round, something it could
not manage four years ago.
	   The Colombian team arrived in the United States as a candidate
to win that tournament, but lost to Romania and the home team and
didn't survive the first round.
	   ``Our goal is to beat Romania,'' midfielder Harold Lozano said.
	   ``If we beat the Romanians, we will face England and Tunisia
with a more positive attitude and good chances of making it to the
second round,'' goalkeeper Farid Mondragon added.
</TEXT>
