<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Romania-Moldova </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Qualifier Romania 5, Moldova 1 
</HEADLINE>
With AP Photos
<TEXT>
	   PLOIESTI, Romania (AP) _ Dominating throughout the match,
Romania beat hapless Moldova 5-1 Saturday in their last warm-up
game before the World Cup final in France.
	   Romania launched attacks from the very beginning, but their
first scoring chance came only in the second part of the first
half.
	   After missing a penalty kick, Gheorghe Popescu of Galatasaray
recovered quickly the ball and scored in the 34th minute.
	   Two minutes later, teammate Gheorge Hagi served Chelsea's Dan
Petrescu in the penalty area, who made it 2-0.
	   After change of sides, Ilie Dumitrescu of Atlanta, after
outdribbling spectacularly several Moldovan defenders, scored in
the 49th minute, shoving in the ball through Moldova goalkeeper
Dinov's legs.
	   Goal number four was a header by Viorel Moldovan in the 74th
minute.
	   The hosts kept attacking, and in the 83rd minute Radu Nicolescu,
positioned in the left corner of the penalty box, lifted the ball
over Moldova's keeper for a 5-0 lead.
	   Moldova's lone goal came from Iuri Tabanov in the 88th who
connected on a rebound.
	   The Romanians will leave Sunday for the French city of Albi,
where they will be accommodated during the tournament.
	   Romania plays in Group G together with England, Colombia and
Tunisia.
	   Lineups
	   Romania: Dumitru Stangaciu, Constantin Galca, Gheorghe Popescu,
Iulian Filipescu, Dan Petrescu, Gheorghe Hagi, Liviu Ciobotariu,
Lucian Marinescu, Dorinel Munteanu, Adrian Ilie, Viorel Moldovan.
	   Moldova: Sergei Dinov, Sergei Stroneco, Ion Testimiteanu,
Alexandru Guzun, Sergei Clescenco, Ghenadie Pusca, Sergiu Chirilov,
Vladimir Gaidamasciuc, Oleg Fistican, Gheorghe Stratulat, Sergei
Epureanu.
	   (ma/rp) 	   
