<HEADLINE>
Romario signs to do World Cup commentary for TV Globo 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) - Romario, Brazil's injured all-star
forward, has been signed by the nation's largest television station
to do World Cup commentary.
	   ``We don't have all the details, but he will work out of Rio de
Janeiro,'' Dario Leite, a sports reporter for TV Globo told the
Associated Press.
	   Leite said Romario will not travel to France because he is
undergoing therapy for his injured right calf. The MVP of the 1994
World Cup was dropped from the national team last Tuesday after it
became apparent that his injury would not recover in time for
Brazil's opener against Scotland on June 10.
	   Back in Rio, Romario's calf has improved much faster than
expected, and he vows to take the field on June 16 with Rio team,
Flamengo.
	   On that day, Brazil will play its second World Cup game against
Morocco.
