w2740 &Cx1f; wstm-
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Soccer-Belgium     06-06 0362
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Belgium-Paraguay </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Belgium defeats Paraguay in World Cup warmup 1-0 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) _ Belgium handed Paraguay its fourth
World Cup warmup defeat in a row Saturday, beating the South
Americans 1-0 on a humid night punctuated by a fierce thunderstorm.
	   Veteran Enzo Scifo got Belgium ahead in the 56th minute with a
lucky goal: his high pass into the penalty area was deflected by a
defender and sailed past goalie Ruben Ruiz Diaz.
	   The loss was Paraguay's fourth World Cup warmup loss. Since May
21, it has lost also to the Czech Republic, the Netherlands and
Romania and drew against Japan.
	   The Belgians have won seven World Cup warmups. They lost one: a
0-2 defeat at the hands of France.
	   Paraguay began cautiously, closing ranks in the back, ceding the
midfield and mounting no serious offense.
	   One notable exception: a hard and low free kick in the 19th
minute by Francisco Arce that flew just past the Belgian goal post.
	   The Belgians created scoring chances but finished off none.
	   The best came in the 40th minute when Luis Oliveira drove the
ball into the goal mouth, faked a movement to the right but passed
to the left to Luc Nilis whose low shot was brilliantly reflected
by Paraguay goal Ruben Ruiz Diaz for a corner shot.
	   Belgium began without play maker Scifo.
	   Coach Georges Leekens put him into the team in the second half.
That was what the Belgians needed. They _ and the match _ came
alive.
	   In the 54th minute a razor-sharp pass by Vital Borkelmans found
Emile Mpenza who outran Catalino Rivarola but his shot went high.
	   In the 55th minute, Scifo made it 1-0 and Belgium came close 2-0
in the 56th. A high pass by Borkelmans sent Mpenza into the air,
but his header bounced hard and high, missing the cross bar by an
inch.
	   Late in the second half, a fierce thunderstorm made for a
slippery and dangerous field in the King Baudouin Stadium where
22,000 people watched the match.
	   In the 85th minute, after some messy soccer in front of the
Belgian goal the ball popped in front of Arce who tried a hard
shot, but missed a viurtually open goal.
 &UR; (rw)	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Sports-Soccer-Belgium-Paraguay; CT:s; 
