<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Copa Libertadores-Vasco-Gremio,0202 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vasco wins semifinals birth in Libertadores Cup tournament 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) - Vasco beat Gremio 1-0 to win a
semifinals berth for the continent-wide Libertadores Cup tournament
Saturday.
	   Vasco, Brazil's 1997 national championship team beat Gremio, a
two-time Libertadores Cup winner at Rio's Sao Januario stadium
before a capacity crowd of 35,000 fans.
	   It was the first time Vasco had ever reached the semifinals.
	   Vasco's Pedrinho scored the game's only goal in the 40th minute
after he converted a perfect pass from Luizao in front of the goal
and tapped it in with his left foot.
	   In the second half, Gremio strikers Guilhereme, Palhinha and
Silvinha kept up a relentless attack on Vasco goalie Caetano, who
made several spectacular saves. Vasco's veteran defender Mauro
Galvao also starred.
	   This was the second game for the coveted semifinals berth
between the two teams. Last Wednesday, they played to a 1-1 tie in
Porto Alegre.
	   In the next round, Vasco will face Argentina's River Plate after
the World Cup in mid-July.
	   The finals for the Libertadores Cup championship won't begin
until Aug. 12
</TEXT>
