<SLUG> BC-Britain-Plane Turbulence </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Four reported hurt in airline flight turbulence 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ An Olympic Airways flight from Athens to Montreal
hit severe turbulence that left four people hurt, including a woman
whose legs were broken, according to the hospital where the injured
were taken after an unscheduled landing in London.
	   No airline spokesman was immediaterly available and few details
were known, but Montreal's Dorval Airport said Olympic flight 423,
which had been scheduled to arrive at 3:15 p.m. local time (2015
GMT), was not expected to reach Montreal until 10 p.m. (0300 GMT
Sunday).
	   London's Heathrow Airport said the Boeing 747 made an
unscheduled landing at 3 p.m. (1400 GMT) so the injured could be
treated.
	   Five Greek women were taken off the plane and moved by ambulance
to Hillingdon Hospital in Uxbridge, about 5 miles (8 km) north of
the airport, said hospital spokesman Mark Purcell.
	   One, who is pregnant, underwent checks at the hospital's
maternity clinic but was given the all clear, he said.
	   The injured were the woman whose legs were broken, two air
hostesses, and a fourth woman kept overnight for observation.
	   ``The two air crew are being treated for head and neck injuries.
The lady with the broken legs is stable and comfortable,'' Purcell
said. No further details were available.
	   (acw)
</TEXT>
