<HEADLINE>
Plane picks up Britons in Eritrea With Eritrea-Ethiopia 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: Updates with British plane to picks up Britons, others 
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ A British air force plane flew into Eritrea on
Saturday night and picked up about 100 foreign nationals who had
been stranded in the East African nation where fighting with
Ethiopia has escalated over their disputed border.
	   An RAF C-130 Hercules picked up the remaining 40 Britons and
about 60 Australian, Canadian and South African nationals, and took
off at around 2200GMT for Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, the Ministry of
Defense said.
	   The aircraft was on the ground for an hour, during which time
the Royal Marines, carrying light weapons, helped to marshal
evacuees and provide protection, the government said.
	   The Foreign Office on Friday advised British citizens in Eritrea
to leave as soon as possible because of the worsening conflict.
	   Forty-eight Britons left Eritrea that night on a U.S. aircraft
which landed in Frankfurt early Saturday. The Foreign Office said
the Britons, mainly working for the non-governmental organization
Voluntary Service Overseas, then flew to London.
	   Ethiopian warplanes .. pvs graf 6
