<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Britain-Running Dog </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Wilma the greyhound comes home 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Wilma the greyhound, who sprinted off the track
after her last race and kept on going, has finally returned to her
trainer after three days on the lam.
	   Wilma came last in her race at a greyhound track in Poole,
southwest England, Tuesday night. But when the other dogs eased up
after the race, Wilma sprinted off through the stadium gates, still
wearing her muzzle and an orange running jacket bearing a number 5.
	   One baffled motorist telephoned police to say he had been
overtaken by a greyhound on a road five miles (8 kilometers) from
Poole.
	   On Friday night, trainer Jo Burridge received a phone call to
say Wilma had been spotted in an industrial park about 3 1/2 miles
(6 km) from the stadium. Mrs. Burridge drove quickly to the spot
and Wilma's wanderings were over.
	   Tail wagging furiously, Wilma was put in the car and driven back
to the kennels, where she tucked into a meaty dinner before bedding
down for the night.
	   ``She's fine and resting and she doesn't seem to have lost any
weight,'' Mrs. Burridge said. ``I'm just pleased to have her back
and she doesn't seem the worst for wear.''
	   (acw)
</TEXT>
