	   By Larry Siddons
	   OZOIR LA FERRIERE, France _ Romario is gone, and the battle is
on for his place in Brazil's starting lineup. For now, Bebeto is
the No. 2 striker, alongside Ronaldo. But Edmundo openly says he
deserves the job, and Denilson could upstage them both once the Cup
starts next Wednesday.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Brazil. Has moved.
	   By Peter Muello
	   GRESSY, France _ Now that they know the first round games they
are handling, the 34 World Cup referees fear they may become the
biggest stars.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-World Cup Refs. Has moved.
	   By Robert Millward
	   MARIGNAC, France _ The 23 goals that Marcelo Salas and Ivan
Zamorano scored in qualifying games are ancient history. ``What
counts now it the ones we will score in the World Cup,'' beginning
with Italy, Salas declares.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Chile. Has moved.
