<HEADLINE>
Celebrity Spotlight and Birthdays 
</HEADLINE>
AP Photo NY374
By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
	   In the spotlight: Keenen Ivory Wayans, living colorfully.
	   Buff, sleek and shaved like a cue ball, Keenen Ivory Wayans is
the trailblazer for one of the funniest clans in show business _
described half-jokingly as the black Osmond family.
	   Wayans' parents were strict disciplinarians and the Wayans kids
soon learned to provide their own entertainment.
	   ``Everything was a joke,'' he recalled. ``If you got a whippin',
when you got back to the table, you heard nine other people doing
impressions of your screaming.''
	   Wayans studied engineering at Alabama's Tuskegee University and
dabbled in stand-up comedy before collaborating with filmmaker
Robert Townsend and comedian Eddie Murphy.
	   Together with brothers Leon, Damon and Marlon, the family teamed
up in 1990 to create the groundbreaking Fox TV hip-hop variety
show, ``In Living Color.''
	   By 1992, Wayans, who turns 40 June 8, feuded with Fox over
creative and financial issues. He quit the Emmy-winning show. He
next concentrated on films, with roles in ``I'm Gonna Git You
Sucka,'' ``The Glimmer Man'' and ``Low Down Dirty Shame.''
Audiences hooted at his spoofs of racial and sexual stereotypes.
	   In August 1997, Wayans tried to win over mainstream audiences as
host of a syndicated late-night series for Disney's Buena Vista
Television. But the show didn't last.
	   ``When you're on the outside looking in, these talk shows don't
appear to be the monsters that they are,'' Wayans said. ``I've
gained much greater respect for the guys that have been doing it
for 10, 15 years.''
	   Last year, he starred in, wrote and produced ``Most Wanted,''
the story of a Marine sniper forced to serve on a team of macho
thugs and professional maulers out to kill the first lady.
	   Celebrity birthdays for June 7-13:
	   June 7: Singer Tom Jones is 58. Actor Ken Osmond (Eddie Haskell
on ``Leave It to Beaver'') is 55. Talk-show host Jenny Jones is 52.
Actor Liam Neeson is 46. The artist formerly known as Prince is 40.
Rapper Ecstacy (Whodini) is 34. Musician Eric Kretz (Stone Temple
Pilots) is 32.
	   June 8: Comedian-talk show host Joan Rivers is 65. Singer Chuck
Negron (Three Dog Night) is 56. Rock musician Mick Box (Uriah Heep)
is 51. Actress Sonia Braga is 48. Actress Kathy Baker (``Picket
Fences'') is 48. Actor Griffin Dunne is 43. Actor-director Keenen
Ivory Wayans is 40. Singer Mick Hucknall (Simply Red) is 38.
Musician Nick Rhodes (Duran Duran) is 36. R and B singer Doris
Pearson (Five Star) is 32. Actress Julianna Margulies is 31. Actor
Dan Futterman is 31. R and B singer Nicci Gilbert (Brownstone) is
28.
	   June 9: Comedian Jackie Mason is 64. Rock musician Jon Lord
(Deep Purple, Whitesnake) is 57. Actor Michael J. Fox is 37. Actor
Johnny Depp is 35. Actress Gloria Reuben is 33. Rock musician Dean
Felber (Hootie and the Blowfish) is 31. Rock musician Dean Dinning
(Toad the Wet Sprocket) is 31. Actress Natalie Portman is 17.
	   June 10: Singer Shirley Alston (The Shirelles) is 57. Actress
Elisabeth Shue is 35. Actress Jeanne Tripplehorn is 35.
Model-actress Elizabeth Hurley is 33. Supermodel Linda Evangelista
is 33. R and B singer Faith Evans is 25. R and B singer Lemisha
Grinstead (702) is 20.
	   June 11: Actor Gene Wilder is 63. Actor Chad Everett is 62.
Singer Joey Dee is 58. Rock musician Frank Beard (ZZ Top) is 49.
Rock singer Donnie Van Zandt (.38 Special) is 46. Rock musician Dan
Lavery (Tonic) is 29. Actor Joshua Jackson (``Dawson's Creek'') is
20.
	   June 12: Singer Vic Damone is 70. Actor-singer Jim Nabors is 68.
Rock singer Reg Presley (The Troggs) is 55. Rock singer-musician
Brad Delp (Boston) is 47. Rock musician Bun E. Carlos (Cheap Trick)
is 47. Actor Timothy Busfield is 41. Rock musician John Linnell
(They Might Be Giants) is 39. Rapper Grandmaster Dee (Whodini) is
36.
	   June 13: Actor Malcolm McDowell is 55. Singer Dennis Locorriere
(Dr. Hook) is 49. Actor Richard Thomas is 47. Comedian Tim Allen is
45. Actress Ally Sheedy is 36. R and B singer Deniece Pearson (Five
Star) is 30. Actor-singer Jamie Walters is 29. Actresses Ashley and
Mary Kate Olsen are 12.
</TEXT>
