<HEADLINE>
BALTIMORE: 4 2-3 innings. Rangers 3, Padres 0 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   In Arlington, Texas, John Burkett pitched eight shutout innings
and Luis Alicea had a two-run double as Texas beat San Diego.
	   Burkett (4-5) allowed five hits, struck out four and walked one
to win for the first time since May 10. John Wetteland pitched the
ninth for his 16th save as the Rangers won for the fourth time in
five games.
	   Alicea had his two-run double in the fifth and Domingo Cedeno
homered in the seventh. San Diego starter Sterling Hitchcock (3-1)
allowed nine hits in 7 2-3 innings.
